            <abstract>
                <p>This short treatise describes the positions of moonrise and moonset in six 'gates' for the twelve Ethiopian months (with the exception of <foreign xml:lang="gez">Ṗāgʷǝmen</foreign>), 
                    starting with <foreign xml:lang="gez">Miyāzyā</foreign>. The arrangment of the gates and months follows that of the 'gates'-type diagrams. The text is related to the concepts transmitted in 
                    <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1340EnochE#Luminaries"></ref>. 
                    Note that <ref type="mss" corresp="BAVet119"/> has an addition <foreign xml:lang="gez">ከመዝ፡ ይሠርቁ፡ በሠርቀ፡ ዕብራውያን፡ ወበወርኃ፡ ዕብራውያን።</foreign> at the 
                    befinning of the text.</p>
            </abstract>
